<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figure 39. Distribution of Solanum pygmaeum in its non-native range in the Old World." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.106.21991.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/218742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">39</figureCitation>
). Native to central and coastal Argentina; a few specimens known from Europe arriving as seeds through wool shipments but these are not usually established as permanent populations.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="1326095" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.106.21991.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/218742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 39" startId="F39">
