<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation status</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Euphytica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B176" refString="IUCN, 2016. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 12. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 12. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2016">IUCN 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in its native range and can be assigned a preliminary status of LC (Least Concern; Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="T7" captionText="Table 7. Preliminary conservation assessments for the Old World members of the Morelloid clade. For details, see Materials and Methods and individual species treatments. Preliminary assessments are based on EOO (Extent of Occurrence) only (see Materials and Methods) and have been calculated for worldwide ranges for each species. The conservation status of species known to be introduced in the Old World has been assessed considering native range only and is discussed under each species treatments." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2FA7BDE3ED0CDC21CAEAEE383BFAB558" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="2FA7BDE3ED0CDC21CAEAEE383BFAB558">7</tableCitation>
). Populations from the Old World are relatively ephemeral. Within the native range in South America, 
<taxonomicName family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. pygmaeum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still has a relatively large EOO of 700,962 km2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only occasionally collected in Europe, usually associated with wool waste. It is a plant that spreads by underground stems, so it is surprising that it has not become established; we include the species here so that old herbarium specimens can be identified and so that the species can be spotted if it does become established as climate changes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The species is easy to distinguish from all other morelloids occurring in Europe by its large flowers (anthers&gt; 3mm long), narrowly elliptic calyx lobes (1.5-1.8 mm long) and rhizomatous habit. Leaves are quite variable in size, but are usually narrowly elliptic, less often wider in the lower half.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We have selected the P duplicates that were part of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Société">&quot;Societe</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="cénomane">cenomane</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’exsicccata”">d'exsicccata&quot;</normalizedToken>
as the lectotypes of var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonte ex Aellen" authorityYear="1940" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum var. integrifolium" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pygmaeum" variety="integrifolium">Solanum pygmaeum integrifolium</taxonomicName>
and var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonte ex Aellen" authorityYear="1940" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum var. sinuatodentatum" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pygmaeum" variety="sinuatodentatum">Solanum pygmaeum sinuatodentatum</taxonomicName>
because they are well-preserved and have both flowers and young fruits. The lectotype we have selected for var. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum var. hastatum" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pygmaeum" variety="hastatum">Solanum pygmaeum hastatum</taxonomicName>
is in an Argentinian herbarium (see best practice as outlined in 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, GF" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1549 - 1551" refId="B340" refString="Smith, GF, Figueiredo, E, 2011. Responsible species description: A change of attitude is needed to facilitate and improve access to biological material. Taxon 60: 1549 - 1551" title="Responsible species description: A change of attitude is needed to facilitate and improve access to biological material." volume="60" year="2011">Smith and Figueiredo 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and we have been unable as yet to trace original material of var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonte ex Aellen" authorityYear="1940" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pygmaeum var. latifolium" order="Centrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pygmaeum" variety="latifolium">Solanum pygmaeum latifolium</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
